               <interp inst="t18460223-807" type="date" value="18460223"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18460223-807-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-807-18460223 t18460223-807-offence-1 t18460223-807-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>807. <persName id="def1-807-18460223" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-807-18460223" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-807-18460223" type="age" value="44"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-807-18460223" type="surname" value="GIBSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-807-18460223" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOSEPH GIBSON</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18460223-807-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18460223-807-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="sexual"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18460223-807-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="bigamy"></interp> for bigamy.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460223-name-898" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-898" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-898" type="surname" value="DAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-898" type="given" value="WILLIAM DAVISON"></interp>WILLIAM DAVISON DAY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable K</hi> 74.) I apprehended the pri<lb></lb>soner at Rotherhithe, on the 12th of Feb.—I told him he was charged with bigamy—he said it would now be settled, and that it was his wish that it should be so—he asked me on our road to the Court what his imprisonment would be—I said I could not tell—he said his second wife knew of his first wife being living at the time, and that she was married again—I went to the church of the Holy Trinity, at Kingston-upon-Hull, on the 19th of Feb.—the mi<lb></lb>nister of the parish showed me the register, and I examined this copy with the orginal—it is correct—this is it—(<hi rend="italic">read</hi>—certifying that Joseph Gibson and Mary Walton were married on the 18th of Dec, 1824.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460223-name-899" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-899" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-899" type="surname" value="JORDESON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-899" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN JORDESON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of a person named Jordeson, living at Hull. I know the prisoner—I was present at his marriage with Mary Walton in 1824—she was alive last week, when I left Hull—she has never been from home—I do not think the prisoner and her lived together above three or four years.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. WILDE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> The prisoner is a seafaring man? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—they lived together three or four years, and had a child—he was away at sea a year and ten months—when he returned his wife was far gone in the family way—that was the reason they parted—they divided the furni<lb></lb>ture and separated—I believe he has been in Hull, but I did not see him—I do not know that he has been there for seventeen years—his wife married again about two years ago.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was there any difficulty in his finding where his first wife was? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460223-name-900" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-900" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-900" type="surname" value="MILES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-900" type="given" value="ELIZA MARY"></interp>ELIZA MARY MILES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a widow. I married the prisoner on the 1st of July, eight years ago, at St. Saviour's, Southwark—I was in no business—I was protected by my brothers, who are since dead.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> The prisoner had been living in the house where you were residing? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, he lodged there—since our marriage my mother and my son have lived in the house—the prisoner has not supported us all—my son has always been employed—I have some property of my own—I married the prisoner in 1838, and have lived with him ever since—my son was mar<lb></lb>ried in the summer—I gave him a bed and bedstead on his marriage.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did that lead to a family dispute? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I understood the prisoner to have been married, and to have been away from home for years, under the circumstances that have been detailed—I expected him to deal fairly by me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. WILDE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did he not tell you he had had no correspondence with his wife for many years, and did not know whether she was alive or dead? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I spoke to Mr. Phillips—he did not advise me to inquire about it—I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184602230179"></xptr>
               <p>did not inquire—I have taken all the furniture from the house, but it was under advice.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18460223-807-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18460223-807-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460223-807-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 44.—<hi rend="italic">Recommended to mercy 
<rs id="t18460223-807-punishment-134" type="punishmentDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18460223-807-punishment-134" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
